
CCAST vs NOAA calibration algorithm comparisons
------------------------------------------------
      
ccast_noaa1: CCAST and NOAA relative FOV response, 17 Dec 2014.

ccast_noaa2: CCAST and NOAA 17–19 Feb 2015 SDR Algorithm Tests,
  15 Apr 2015.

ccast_noaa3: new CrIS calibration algorithm comparisons, 5 Aug 2015.

ccast_noaa4: CrIS extended resolution calibration algorithm
  comparisons, May 10 2016.  This report interesting because it's
  an extensive comparison of ccast with flat reference truth and
  NOAA with reference truth convolved with responsivity, with all
  other params except the basic algorithm fixed.  The difference
  between resp and flat reference truth is significant, around 0.2K
  or more in several places.  To summarize, NOAA needs to convolve
  its validation tests with instrument responsivity to get results
  comparable to ccast validated with "flat" (sinc basis) reference
  truth.
  
